			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">I have boiled this down to a small test case that does not use NaCl.  In short, pointing %cs to an LDT entry seems to be completely broken on the 64-bit kernels.  Although a single lcall will work, repeated lcalls eventually crash the process or the machine.  No multi-threading is required, although I suspect that using multiple threads might trigger a kernel panic sooner (it is hard to be sure because the test/reboot cycle is slow).</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-06-22T19:58:23.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-06-22T19:58:23.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 1 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1930#c1" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1930/comments/full/1" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>